# Developer Portal — Agent Context

## Local secrets

Secrets are loaded from `src/developer-portal/.env` (git-ignored).
`docker-compose.dev.yml` passes them into the backend container via environment variables.

Required variables:

| Variable | Purpose | Minimum scope |
|---|---|---|
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | GitHub integration (catalog ingestion, scaffolder) | `repo` |
| `AZURE_TOKEN` | Azure DevOps integration (scaffolder `publish:azure` action) | Code (Read & Write) — `vso.code_write` |

To populate, edit `.env`:

```
GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_pat_here
AZURE_TOKEN=your_azure_devops_pat_here
```

### Azure DevOps PAT notes
- Create at `https://dev.azure.com/{org}/_usersSettings/tokens`
- **Code (Read & Write)** scope is sufficient to create repositories via the REST API
- The token scope controls capability, but your account also needs the **Create Repository**
  project-level permission; if repo creation returns 403 after auth is working, a project
  admin must grant that permission
